6:
Ngh... Has it always been this windy
in Palpebra?
10:
Probably a storm coming in. I dunno
about you guys, but I'd prefer to stay
dry, so we'd best get movin'.
20:
Such handsome eyes... Such
luxurious hair!
23:
Yes, yes, yes! Joyous day! It's
you—the one destined to become
my hazubando!
29:
Come, come! Let us announce our
vows before the village and restore
its glory!
33:
Our what now?!
Do I even know you?
38:
Where are my manners? My name
is Shywe. I am the one destined to
become your wyfu—as foretold by
the sprites!
45:
Oh, so sorry! In your tongue it would
mean, hmm... how to say this... Ah,
yes! Holy matrimony!
56:
Er, I mean, I've never even met
you—what are you trying to pull
here?!
61:
Pull? There is no pulling here. Only
the sacred guidance of the sprites!
66:
You can't expect me to go along
with this, can you?!
71:
Obviously! And I don't think I
appreciate your tone, mister!
75:
...Are you seriously getting MAD at
me?
78:
Hehe... Look at us—already having
our first fight! This might hurt a
teeeeensy-weensy bit, okay?
84: Get down, Alk! We'll take care of this!
92:
So my hazubando likes to play hard
to get, I see!
96:
Eyes over here, lady! You're dealin'
with me now!
107:
*pant* *wheeze* I think I lost her... for
now, at least.
111:
Teehee... Just where do you think
you're going?
115: I didn't lose her at all!
119:
Can you... at least... tell me... why we
have to get... married?!
123:
It's part of the prophecy! In order for
our dwindling village to survive, the
blood of outsiders would be
necessary.
126:
The prophecy? I don't know anything
about that! And furthermore, why
me? We've just met!
130:
Do you have a problem with our
arrangement?
139:
There's nothing for you to be worried
about, my dear! My father is the
chief, after all. You'll be welcomed
with open arms!
141:
I promise you'll love it—feast on our
delicious fuudo, sleep on the fluffiest
of beddo, and have every whim and
fancy catered by our loyal meido!
144:
In other words, you'll live like a king!
With me as your queen.
148:
That sounds lovely and all, but...
don't I get a say in all this?! What
about MY rights?
152:
They told me outsiders would be
quite spirited, but I didn't expect THIS
much resistance!
153:
Are your rights and opinions really
so important?
160:
Rather than brave the  winds and
seas of life alone, wouldn't you
rather be bound to a greater power
to guide your way?
161:
Become one with the sprites, and
you will feel no such pain any longer.
168:
How many kids do you want? I think
five would be good, right?
171:
But if you want more, I'll try my
hardest to give you up to ten, even!
178:
Aren't YOU upset about having to
marry someone you've only just met?
184: Let's get going now, shall we?
193:
That's right! Just as you have your
culture, I have my own! And where
I'm from, we're not allowed to marry
until we turn eighteen!
196:
And there's, uh, no way around this
law! Such a shame, right? Heh...
202:
Such a shame.
Oh well! I'm sure the sprites will allow
it!
210:
You couldn't possibly go against the
word of the sprites, right? Well, uh,
the same goes for me!
213:
Where I'm from, there is nothing
more hallowed and sacred than the
law! If you can't accept my values,
how can you expect me to accept
yours?
218:
That DOES make sense. It would be
troublesome for us both if you
weren't able to open yourself to the
sprites...
221:
I suppose it can't be helped... Clearly
there is a clash between your
culture and the will of the sprites.
223:
But I'm sure there was a reason you
were chosen. I suppose I'll just have
to see this through for myself!
226: What are you getting at, exactly?
229:
Isn't it obvious? I'll be joining you
instead!
232:
I'm sure there will be much for me to
learn, but I'll do everything I can to
become the wyfu of your dreams!
236:
Hoo, boy... I've got a bad feeling
about this.
